* Leonard Cohen - SELECTED POEMS, 1956-1968 (Viking, 1968).  255 pp. -- PDF


Published soon after the release of Leonard Cohen's first album in 1967, SELECTED POEMS contains a generous selection of material from volumes previously published only in Canada.  It includes many of the ecstatically lyric poems first published in &quot;The Spice-Box of Earth&quot; (1961), as well as verses from &quot;Let Us Compare Mythologies&quot; (1956), &quot;Flowers for Hitler&quot; (1964), &quot;Parasites of Heaven&quot; (1966), and a number of new poems collected for the first time, many with strong social and religious overtones.

In his eloquent search for what he calls a &quot;state of grace&quot; -- the kind of balance with which one rises to the chaos around him -- Cohen eludes the restrictions of genres and generations.  Eclectic, searching, his voice is above all deeply personal.

